WorkFlow
--------------------------------------------------
Commit
Clone
Tracking/Untracking : Tracking done by .git folder to track git files.

Commands
--------------------------------------------------
Clone repository(Existing)    : git clone <Repo url>
Clone repository(New)         : git clone <Repo url> <Name>
Make Directory                : mkdir <Name>
Change Directory              : cd <Name>
List files                    : ls
List Hidden Files             : ls -al
To know Git Status            : git status
To Know Content differences   : git diff
To add file to staging area   : git add <FileName>
To commit file to Local Git   : git commit -m "Commit Message"
Add Commit Full Information   : git commit -v
To push file to Remote GitHub : git push <server> <branch>
To see is history of Commits  : git log
To see commit differences     : git log -p
To see only last 2 commits    : git log -2
To see commits in single line : git log --pretty=oneline
Every commits in single line  : git log --oneline
Create new file               : touch <filename>
Open file in vi editor        : vi <filename>
Check content of File         : cat <filename>
Check Remote REPO Server      : git remote


How to Push Local Directory to GitHub
------------------------------------------------
Initialize Git                : git init
Git Status                    : git status
Add file                      : git add <filename1> <filename2>
Add all files                 : git add .
Commit all files              : git commit -m "Commit Message"
Add remote server             : git remote add <server> <repourl>
Push files to Github          : git push -u <server> <branch> Ex: git push -u origin main

How to Create Git Ignore file
------------------------------------------------------
Create GIT IGNORE File        : vi .gitignore

How to Create Branch Name
-------------------------------------------------
Create Branch Name            : git branch <branch-name>
Move to Branch Name           : git checkout <branch-name>
All Branches commits          : git log --oneline --all
Create Branch and Switch      : git checkout -b <branch-name>
Merge Branch                  : git merge <branch-name>
Delete Branch                 : git branch -d <branch-name>
Know Merged Branches          : git branch --merge
Know not Merged Branches      : git branch --no-merge

How to Pull and Fetch Repository
Fetch Repo Server             : git fetch <server-name>
Pull All changes from git     : git pull <server-name>

How to create Git Tag
Create Git tag               : git tag <tag>
List git tag                 : git tag
Compare Tag                  : git diff <tag1> <tag2>
Delete Tag                   : git tag -d <tag>
Give Tag to Commit           : git tag -a <version> <commitnumber>
Update Tag to Commit         : git tag -a <version> -f <commitnumber>
Push Tags                    : git push <server> <tagname>
Push All Tags                : git push <server> --tags
List Specific Tags           : git tag -list "v1.*"


